{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"bowl, round cookie cutter (3 cm), serving platter, refrigerator","id":"r123526","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-NJFaZslrOX4\/XZam-7-JPBI\/AAAAAAAAg4Y\/OmpIklVRwxwY1ZjYTWFZ4gbHY6bWl8ouwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_-gLz4y4p4DVz9pWB.png","title":"Watermelon and Salmon Ceviche Stack","publishedAt":"2017-04-24T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"½ fresh jalapeño chilli, deseeded and cut into halves"},{"content":"4 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only"},{"content":"20 g red onion"},{"content":"2 pinches ground cumin"},{"content":"2 pinches ground smoked paprika"},{"content":"2 pinches fine sea salt, to taste"},{"content":"2 pinches ground black pepper, to taste"},{"content":"2 tsp avocado oil"},{"content":"20 g lime juice (approx. 1 lime)"},{"content":"250 g fresh boneless, skinless salmon fillet, cut into pieces (1 cm)"},{"content":"800 - 1000 g watermelon (approx. ¼ watermelon)"},{"content":"½ avocado, flesh only, cut into cubes (1 cm)"},{"content":"2 - 3 drops Tabasco sauce, to serve (optional)"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"3.2 g","fat":"2.8 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"2.8 g","calories":"209 kJ \/ 49 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Place jalapeño, coriander and red onion in mixing bowl then chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add cumin, paprika, salt, pepper, avocado oil, lime juice and salmon then combine <b>1-2 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Transfer ceviche into a ceramic or glass bowl, then place into refrigerator to allow flavours to infuse for 10 minutes."},{"content":"Cut watermelon into 1 cm slices, then using a round cookie cutter (Ø 3 cm), cut out 20-25 watermelon rounds. Place rounds onto a serving platter."},{"content":"Placing cookie cutter back over watermelon round to use as a mould, spoon 1 tsp salmon ceviche onto watermelon and spread out to edges (this ensures a neat shape). Carefully remove cookie cutter, then repeat with remaining watermelon rounds and ceviche."},{"content":"Place a few small cubes of avocado on top of each ceviche stack with a few drops of Tabasco sauce (optional). Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This dish is best served immediately, however you can cut out the watermelon rounds in advance and store in the refrigerator for 1-2 hours before making the salmon ceviche. We don't advise making the ceviche component in advance as the citric acid in the fruit will continue to \"cook\" the salmon the longer it sits."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","25m","25 pieces"]}